Description of 
holotype
.

Capitalized color codes follow a standard guide (

Smithe 
1975

; 

1981

). Forehead and crown are blackish-gray (Black Neutral Gray 
82
), with a dusky brown tinge on the sides (near Dusky Brown 
19
) and a large semi-concealed white patch on the midcrown formed by white feathers with dark gray tips (Dark Neutral Gray 
83
). The crown becomes paler (shading to Dark Neutral Gray 
83
) posteriorly, blending to olive gray on the nape (near Glaucous 
79
) and to dark olive green (between Basic and Auxiliary Olive Green 
46–47
) on the upper back. Scapulars, back, rump, and upper tail-coverts are also olive green but brighter (Bunting Green 
150
).
